<TITLE> UN considering Dhaka as a policymaker in peacekeeping </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com)A top UN official has said Bangladesh's participation in the policymaking of the peacekeeping mission is under consideration. Under-secretary-general (peacekeeping opeartions) Alain Le Roy on Thursday made the comment before the media after his meeting with foreign minister Dipu Moni at her office. Roy said the UN will deploy 140 female police officers from Bangladesh in different peacekeeping missions around the world. UN has plans to establish a regional centre of the mission at Dhaka, he added. Bangladesh is currently the second largest contributor of UN peacekeeping troops, out of 116 countries, with 9,849 military and police deployed overseas. On Sep 26, in her UNGA speech in Bangla, prime minister Sheikh Hasina had called for proportional representation of Bangladesh in planning and strategising the UN peacekeeping operations and sought support of member countries to make Bangla an official language of the world body. Roy, on a two-day tour to Bangladesh, has met with the prime minister and the army chief. bdnews
